  "text": "The optimal result is obviously given by single-user Mercury/waterfilling algorithm, where user k should consider other users' interference as noise, and therefore contradicts the initial assumption. This proof is true for any user k = 1, . . . , K. At the global optimal point, each user should satisfy single-user Mercury/waterfilling condition, which is a necessary condition. In addition, at global optimal, single-user Mercury/waterfilling indicates that each user must allocate all its available power, providing therefore an explanation for power constraint [CITATION_1] .",
